Short:    NList custom classes for MUI (v0.96)
Author:   NList Open Source Team
Uploader: Sebastian Bauer <mail@sebastianbauer.info>
Type:     dev/mui
Requires: MUI 3.6+, OS 2.x (V37+), HotkeyString.mcc from Allan Odgaard
Version:  0.96
Replaces: dev/mui/MCC_NList.lha

Introduction
~~~~~~~~~~~~
This is a MUI custom class package containing replacements for
List/Listtree/Listview/Floattext MUI default class.

The NList/NListview/NFloattext classes originally have been
developed by Gilles Masson. The NListtree classes originally
have been develeoped by Carsten Scholling.

NList classes are available for OS3, OS4 and MorphOS.

The NList classes project is hosted on SourceForge. Its project
name is "nlist-classes".

To report bugs use the bug tracker at
 http://www.sf.net/projects/nlist-classes

Features
~~~~~~~~
Actually the horizontal scrolling is fully supported, there are
smooth scrolling, word wrap support, built-in copy to clipboard,
classic char selection possibility, drag and drop and many other
features. The user can change the column width with mouse and
column titles can act as buttons.

There is a pref class NListviews.mcp with it, which permit the
user to choose all default backgrounds, pens and fonts, scrollbars
mode, drag and drop mode, multiselect mode, keys and qualifiers and
some others.

Included is a Floattext.mui replacement which use NFloattext.mcc,
permitting copy to clipboard and key moving.

Versions
~~~~~~~~
Current MCC_NList classes versions are :

NList.mcc         20.115    16.12.2004
NListview.mcc     19.70     16.12.2004
NFloattext.mcc    19.51     16.12.2004
NListviews.mcp    19.66     16.12.2004
NListtree.mcc     18.22     16.12.2004
NListtree.mcp     18.10     16.12.2004


Overview of changes since NList 0.95
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
- Merged NList and NListtree into one package
- Ported to OS4
- Added new NList option to disallow centering of the list lines.
  This looks better if you have enabled solid window sizing.
- Some bug fixes

The detailed change log can be found in the ChangeLog file.

